notesStmt.note: Title from caption title of predominant work (f. 1r).

First work, incipit and explicit: (f. 1r) [heading] Quarta pars doctrinae de casibus conscientiae, posita in consideratione poenarum ecclesiasticarum. [text] Consideratio poenarum ecclesiasticarum ad modum utilis est sacerdotibus ... (f. 364v) domicidis fortuito.

Second work, incipit and explicit: (f. 366r) [title page] Literae processus S.D.N.D. Clementis Papae VIII/lecta die Coenae Domini: An. 1598./Romae/Apud impressores Camorales/MCXCVI. ... (f. 367r) [heading] Clemens Episcopus/Servus servorum Dei/Ad futuram rei memoriam/Prooemium Bullae/ [incipit of text] Pastoralis Romani Pontificis vigilantia ... (f. 378v) ista piacula salvat.
Third work, incipit: (f. 380r) Quanti momenti sit haec consideratio ... .

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Contains text of a work entitled De casibus conscientiae (f. 1r-364v). There is no indication of the identity of the author. Also contains the text of Pope Clement VIII's bull Pastoralis Romani Pontificis vigilantia (commonly referred to as In coena Domini; f. 366r-378v). This appears to have been copied from a version printed in 1596, though the heading bears the date 1598. Also contains a commentary on Clement's bull, titled De casibus reservatis, et nominatim de iis qui reservatur in bulla Coenae domini.

supportDesc.extent: 500 leaves : 133 x 87 (104 x 57) mm. bound to 137 x 95 mm

collation.p: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 500 + i (contemporary paper); 1-14⁸, 15⁸(-1), 16-24⁸, 25⁶, 26-47⁸, 48⁶, 49-63⁸; [1-499]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 34-37 long lines; ruled in drypoint.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by several hands.

binding.p: Contemporary limp vellum; ties have been removed. Cover almost completely detached, along with back endleaf; cover attached only tenuously at spine and back hinge. Some evidence of water damage and slight mildew damage. Front unnumbered folio partially torn or eaten away.
